			<section id="one" class="main special">
				<div class="container">
					<span class="image fit primary"><img src="images/pic01.jpg" alt="" /></span>
					<div class="content">
						<header class="major">
							<h2>About Me</h2>
						</header>

						<div class="box alt"><div class="row uniform 50%">
						<div class="12u"><span class="image fit"><img src="images/pic010.jpg" alt="" /></span></div></div></div>

<p> Hello! I am Søren Asmussen, working
in applied probability.<br>
I was born in 1946 and started my PhD studies in classical 
branching processes in 1972, but switched areas around 1980.
Since then, my main research
themes have been queueing theory, insurance risk, and simulation methodology (a bit of mathematical finance and statistics too).
</p>
<p>Since February 1, 2003, I have been a Professor of Applied Probability at
Aarhus University, Denmark (expected retirement at the end of
2017). Earlier long-term appointments are at the universities in Copenhagen,
Aalborg and Lund (Sweden). </p>

<p>
In general, I enjoy nature. In earlier days, I made a fair amount of mountaineering (on the easy scale, mainly glacier hiking and easy rock routes). I also enjoy music and play the organ, and I like to cook.
</p>


Curriculum vitae: 
	<a href="assets/cv_short.pdf"> Summary </a>
	<a href="http://home.math.au.dk/asmus/cvhp.pdf">Full</a>
<br>
 	
