						<header class="major">
						<h2>News</h2>
						</header>
						
						<h3>Recent publications</h3>

						<p>
						Submitted:
						<ul>
						<li>(with J. Lehtomaa) Distinguishing log-concavity from heavy tails.</li>
						<li>(with P. Ernst & J. Hasenbein) Stability and tail asymptotics in a multiclass queue with state dependent arrival rates.</li>
						<li>(with J. Thøgersen) Markov dependence in renewal equations and random sums with heavy tails.</li>
						</ul>
						

						Most recent preprints are available from
						<a href="http://www.thiele.au.dk">The Thiele Center</a> 
						<br>
						<a href="http://home.math.au.dk/asmus/publ/publhp.pdf">Full publication list</a><br></p>

						<h3>Applied Probability Symposium in Greenland</h3>



						<p>
						<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/32911979@N00/30065746575/in/album-72157671258978993/">
						<div class="box alt"><div class="row uniform 50%">
						<div class="12u"><span class="image fit"><img src="images/greenland.jpg" alt="" /></span></div></div></div></a>

						<a href="http://thiele.au.dk/events/conferences/2016/ilulissat/">Conference homepage</a><br><br>

						Thanks to Leonardo for collating the highlights of the
						<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/32911979@N00/collections/72157672171786731/">conference photos</a><br>


						</p>

						<h3>Journal of Applied Probability</h3>
						<p> 
							Starting January 1, 2016, Peter Glynn from Stanford University will take over as Editor-in-Chief of the Applied Probability Journals.<br><br>
							
							I started as co-editor (with C.C. Heyde) of the Applied Probability Journals in April 2005, and was the sole Editor-in-Chief from January 2008.</p>

						<h3>Recent awards</h3>
						
						<p>
						<a href="http://home.math.au.dk/asmus/HW.html">Honorary Doctorate at Heriot-Watt University 2013</a><br>
						<a href="http://home.math.au.dk/asmus/sobolev.html">Sobolev Gold Medal 2011</a><br>
						<a href="http://www.informs.org/Recognize-Excellence/INFORMS-Prizes-Awards/John-von-Neumann-Theory-Prize">John von Neumann Theory Prize 2010</a>
						</p>

						<h3>65 years birthday event</h3>
						<p>
						<a href="http://thiele.au.dk/events/conferences/2011/asmussen/">Conference site</a>
						</p>

						<h3>Phase-type software package</h3>
						
						<b>EMpht</b> is a program for fitting
						phase-type distributions to data or parametric distributions. The method
						is described in S. Asmussen, O. Nerman &amp; M. Olsson, Fitting phase-type
						distribution via the EM algorithm, <I>Scand. J. Statist.</I> <B>23</B>, 419-441
						(1996). You must download three files:
						<BR>
						<A HREF="http://home.imf.au.dk/asmus/dl/EMusersguide.ps">EMusersguide.ps</A>
						&nbsp;
						<A HREF="http://home.imf.au.dk/asmus/dl/EMpht.c">EMpht.c</A>
						&nbsp;
						<A HREF="http://home.imf.au.dk/asmus/dl/PHplot.m">PHplot.m</A><BR>
						&nbsp;<BR>
						</p>
					</div>
