							<h2>Books </h2>
						</header>

						<section>

						<h4>Ruin Probabilities (Second edition)</h4>
						<h5>Second edition, World Scientific 2010</h5>
						<h5>First edition, World Scientific 2000</h5>
						<p>
						The second edition was co-authored with 
						<a href="http://www.hec.unil.ch/halbrecher/">Hansjoerg Albrecher</a>
						(University of Lausanne). <br><br>

						Links, second edition:
						<a href="http://www.worldscibooks.com/mathematics/7431.html/">World Scientific Press</a><br>
						<a href="http://www.hec.unil.ch/halbrecher/rp2.html">Corrections and amendments</a><br>
						<br>
						Links, first edition:
						<a href="http://www.wspc.com.sg/books/mathematics/2779.html">World Scientific Press</a>
						<a href="http://www.maths.lth.se/matstat/staff/asmus/rpcontent.ps">Contents</a><br>
						<a href="http://www.maths.lth.se/matstat/staff/asmus/books/rtcorr.ps">Corrections and amendments</a><br> 
						</p>

						<h4>Stochastic Simulation. Algorithms and Analysis</h4>
						<h5>Springer-Verlag 2007</h5>
						<p>
						Co-authored with  <a href="http://icme.stanford.edu/faculty/glynn/">Peter W. Glynn</a> 
						(Stanford University). The book gives a broad survey of Monte Carlo simulation 
						at an intermediate to advanced level. 

						<!-- The book has gradually developed from the following lecture notes.  -->
						<br><br>

						Links: <a href="agcontent.pdf">Table of Contents</a><br>
						<a href="isim08.html">Outstanding Simulation Publication Award 2008</a>
						<a href="agtypos.pdf">Corrections and amendments</a><br>
						</p>

						<!-- <h4>Stochastic Simulation. With a View Towards Stochastic Processes. </h4>
						<h5>Lecture Notes <b>2</b>, MaPhySto, Aarhus, 1999 </h5>

						<p>
						This was written for a concentrated advanced course in Aarhus 1999.
						All of these notes are covered by the book with Glynn, so they are no longer available at the web.
						</p>
						 -->

						<h4>Applied Probability and Queues</h4>
						<h5>Second edition, Springer 2003</h5>
						<h5>First edition, Wiley 1987</h5>
						<p> <a href="apqcontent.ps">Contents</a><br>
						 <a href="apqcorr.pdf">Corrections and amendments</a><br>
						</p>

						<h4>Branching Processes</h4>
						<h5>Birkh&auml;user 1983</h5>
						<p>Co-authored with H. Hering (retired).</p>
